1176
00:55:43,712 --> 00:55:45,482
Yes, it's quite alike.

1177
00:55:46,722 --> 00:55:50,152
(Beef bourguignon: France's traditional beef stew)

1178
00:55:50,652 --> 00:55:53,322
(Using beef with less fat, such as brisket and shin fore shank)

1179
00:55:53,622 --> 00:55:56,292
(Adding in red wine and broth)

1180
00:55:56,692 --> 00:55:59,502
(Boiling it for over 2 hours)

1181
00:56:00,062 --> 00:56:03,932
(It's France's national festive dish.)

1182
00:56:04,402 --> 00:56:07,142
(In short, France's version of braised beef ribs.)

1183
00:56:07,642 --> 00:56:10,842
(Usually enjoyed with bread,)

1184
