(It's been 40 minutes since opening.)

1309
01:02:06,862 --> 01:02:09,872
(At the time, Single Pan House is...)

1310
01:02:10,272 --> 01:02:13,042
(a full house for the outdoor seats.)

1311
01:02:13,302 --> 01:02:16,342
(4 teams of customers are indoors.)

1312
01:02:16,572 --> 01:02:18,481
(Current sales: 13,805 euros in total)

1313
01:02:18,482 --> 01:02:19,582
Good.

1314
01:02:20,182 --> 01:02:21,512
The customers really like it.

1315
01:02:23,452 --> 01:02:26,552
(Glancing at delicious braised beef ribs)

1316
01:02:26,852 --> 01:02:29,922
(The pot was full of braised beef ribs at the start.)

1317
01:02:30,692 --> 01:02:34,062
(Thanks to many customers, it decreased significantly.)

1318
01:02:34,522 --> 01:02:37,232
(They need to refill braised beef ribs.)

1319
01:02:37,762 --> 01:02:40,702
(Tasting before refilling)

1320
01:02:43,502 --> 01:02:44,502
Goodness.

1321
01:02:44,902 --> 01:02:46,102
- Is it sick?
- Yes.

1322
01:02:47,302 --> 01:02:50,072
(He lifts up the sick hotel pan.)

1323
01:02:50,672 --> 01:02:53,882
(Here comes the refill.)

1324
01:02:54,012 --> 01:02:56,982
(Braised beef ribs have reset.)

1325
01:02:58,152 --> 01:02:59,582
The lunch business is incredible.

1326
01:02:59,722 --> 01:03:01,652
- It's doing so well today.
- Yes.

1327
01:03:01,692 --> 01:03:06,022
(Customers arrive right at that moment.)

1328
01:03:06,822 --> 01:03:08,331
(They enter without hesitation.)

1329
01:03:08,332 --> 01:03:09,432
Hello.

1330
01:03:11,732 --> 01:03:15,532
(They gesture someone over. They are...)

1331
01:03:16,202 --> 01:03:19,272
- They're my parents.
- Hello.

1332
01:03:19,872 --> 01:03:20,872
(Si Jin's parents visit Single Pan House.)

1333
01:03:20,873 --> 01:03:23,042
- Nice to meet you.
- You're her parents.

1334
01:03:24,242 --> 01:03:28,512
(Si Jin is a mix of both parents.)

1335
01:03:28,712 --> 01:03:30,081
- It's nice to see you.
- Welcome.

1336
01:03:30,082 --> 01:03:33,181
- Shall I take them upstairs?
- Yes, let's take them upstairs.

1337
01:03:33,182 --> 01:03:35,391
(She feels shy and acts awkward with her parents.)

1338
01:03:35,392 --> 01:03:37,391
Excuse me, Si Jin's parents came to eat.

1339
01:03:37,392 --> 01:03:40,292
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1340
01:03:40,322 --> 01:03:41,631
- Hello.
- Hello.

1341
01:03:41,632 --> 01:03:42,692
Roxana.

1342
01:03:43,092 --> 01:03:44,532
Hello.

1343
01:03:45,702 --> 01:03:48,062
Nice to meet you.

1344
01:03:48,572 --> 01:03:50,771
- She's doing so well.
- Hello.

1345
01:03:50,772 --> 01:03:52,002
Hello.

1346
01:03:52,202 --> 01:03:55,272
(We'll take you to the 2nd floor.)

1347
01:03:55,742 --> 01:03:57,041
Is any table reserved?

1348
01:03:57,042 --> 01:03:59,511
- No, there's no reservation.
- Can we sit anywhere?

1349
01:03:59,512 --> 01:04:01,212
Do you want to sit at a table for four?

1350
01:04:01,512 --> 01:04:04,151
Shall we sit here? A table for four?

1351
01:04:04,152 --> 01:04:06,522
(Si Jin looks sulky too for some reason.)

1352
01:04:06,922 --> 01:04:09,022
(This is how Si Jin normally acts.)

1353
01:04:09,652 --> 01:04:12,492
(She approaches customers with a smile.)

1354
01:04:12,692 --> 01:04:13,721
(Hello.)

1355
01:04:13,722 --> 01:04:15,392
(She greets customers with a high-pitched greeting.)

1356
01:04:15,932 --> 01:04:18,232
(Sometimes, she's bubbly.)

1357
01:04:18,602 --> 01:04:21,132
(Si Jin was a friendly person.)

1358
01:04:21,402 --> 01:04:22,671
- It's okay.
- It's fine?

1359
01:04:22,672 --> 01:04:23,971
There's no table for two now.

1360
01:04:23,972 --> 01:04:25,771
- Here?
- Can't we just split up the tables?

1361
01:04:25,772 --> 01:04:27,072
No.

1362
01:04:28,642 --> 01:04:30,011
Sit here?

1363
01:04:30,012 --> 01:04:32,342
(Si Jin's parents take their seats.)

1364
01:04:33,912 --> 01:04:37,112
(Another customer enters!)

1365
01:04:38,452 --> 01:04:39,482
Hello.

1366
01:04:40,052 --> 01:04:41,581
Do you have a table for two?

1367
01:04:41,582 --> 01:04:43,892
Two, yes. Is upstairs okay?

1368
01:04:44,452 --> 01:04:47,091
Please take him upstairs.

1369
01:04:47,092 --> 01:04:48,562
(2 customers, including a customer who's joining late, are here.)

1370
01:04:49,062 --> 01:04:52,262
(A polite customer joins the 2nd floor.)

1371
01:04:53,232 --> 01:04:54,331
Here.

1372
01:04:54,332 --> 01:04:56,402
(1 more team joins the 2nd floor yet again.)

1373
01:04:56,572 --> 01:04:58,031
- Would you like to sit here?
- Sure.

1374
01:04:58,032 --> 01:04:59,772
(Customers enter one after another.)

1375
01:04:59,942 --> 01:05:01,042
Welcome.

1376
01:05:02,512 --> 01:05:05,282
(As customers enter nonstop)

1377
01:05:06,712 --> 01:05:08,351
The business is doing so well today.

1378
01:05:08,352 --> 01:05:09,352
(Single Pan House has really become a banquet hall.)

1379
01:05:09,582 --> 01:05:12,352
(Let's surpass 1 million dollars and go all the way!)

1380
01:05:13,022 --> 01:05:17,792
(Meanwhile, Si Jin's parents are reading the menu thoroughly.)

1381
01:05:18,022 --> 01:05:21,892
Would it be too much if we ordered two servings of braised beef ribs?

1382
01:05:21,932 --> 01:05:25,231
No, it should be fine.

1383
01:05:25,232 --> 01:05:27,632
(2 braised beef ribs)

1384
01:05:28,132 --> 01:05:31,102
(She takes the orders of the other tables too.)

1385
01:05:31,372 --> 01:05:34,042
(3 braised beef ribs)

1386
01:05:35,172 --> 01:05:37,072
(2 braised beef ribs)

1387
01:05:37,442 --> 01:05:39,682
(Si Jin is taking the orders on the 1st floor.)

1388
01:05:39,782 --> 01:05:42,512
- Tteokbokki.
- Okay, we'll have that, and then...

1389
01:05:43,582 --> 01:05:46,552
(2 braised beef ribs, 1 tteokbokki, 2 sparkling water)

1390
01:05:47,022 --> 01:05:49,522
(Keying in the orders in order)

1391
01:05:50,222 --> 01:05:52,592
(He spots the orders.)

1392
01:05:54,322 --> 01:05:55,992
Three people, two people.

1393
01:05:56,292 --> 01:05:57,561
Five in total.

1394
01:05:57,562 --> 01:05:59,602
(New orders come rushing in.)

1395
01:06:00,202 --> 01:06:04,402
(He wears new gloves at the new orders.)

1396
01:06:05,032 --> 01:06:09,442
(He places cod pancakes on the griddle first.)

1397
01:06:09,942 --> 01:06:12,612
(Plating up tteokbokki)

1398
01:06:13,012 --> 01:06:15,412
(He sends out tteokbokki quickly.)

1399
01:06:16,182 --> 01:06:18,922
(Flipping each pancake in one shot)

1400
01:06:19,182 --> 01:06:20,822
Table Seven, cod pancakes.

1401
01:06:21,382 --> 01:06:23,221
- This is for Table 5.
- This is for Table 5.

1402
01:06:23,222 --> 01:06:26,361
Okay, so we have some cod pancakes as an appetizer.

1403
01:06:26,362 --> 01:06:28,222
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1404
01:06:29,032 --> 01:06:32,531
- This is cod pancakes.
- Gosh, cod pancakes.

1405
01:06:32,532 --> 01:06:34,031
- Bon appetit.
- Thank you.

1406
01:06:34,032 --> 01:06:35,172
Okay.

1407
01:06:36,932 --> 01:06:38,801
(A piece of cod pancake to whet their appetite)

1408
01:06:38,802 --> 01:06:41,402
Okay, bon appetit.

1409
01:06:45,282 --> 01:06:46,441
(Humming)

1410
01:06:46,442 --> 01:06:48,412
(Lifting his eyebrows)

1411
01:06:49,582 --> 01:06:52,682
(Roxana carries the tteokbokki like it's precious.)

1412
01:06:53,122 --> 01:06:55,021
(It's delicious.)

1413
01:06:55,022 --> 01:06:56,592
A small present.

1414
01:06:58,422 --> 01:07:00,061
- Thank you.
- Bon appetit.

1415
01:07:00,062 --> 01:07:02,062
(The tteokbokki is on the house so they can taste it.)

1416
01:07:02,532 --> 01:07:04,792
I'll try first and see if it's spicy.

1417
01:07:08,872 --> 01:07:09,972
It isn't that spicy.

1418
01:07:12,172 --> 01:07:15,712
(After hearing that it's not spicy, he picks up a piece of fish cake.)

1419
01:07:15,872 --> 01:07:18,071
It's more on the sweet side.

1420
01:07:18,072 --> 01:07:20,241
(It's just nice for Mom.)

1421
01:07:20,242 --> 01:07:22,112
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

1422
01:07:22,752 --> 01:07:24,812
(I'm not okay.)

1423
01:07:25,452 --> 01:07:26,482
It's spicy, right?

1424
01:07:26,682 --> 01:07:28,352
(He just laughs.)

1425
01:07:29,292 --> 01:07:30,921
- I should have it with rice.
- Sorry?

1426
01:07:30,922 --> 01:07:31,991
With rice.

1427
01:07:31,992 --> 01:07:33,222
(Since it's spicy)

1428
01:07:33,722 --> 01:07:35,732
Get ready for a pan for two.

1429
01:07:36,992 --> 01:07:38,731
- For two?
- Yes.

1430
01:07:38,732 --> 01:07:39,932
(It's time for braised beef ribs, which will be eaten with rice.)

1431
01:07:40,162 --> 01:07:42,732
(Boiling braised beef ribs)

1432
01:07:43,102 --> 01:07:46,102
(Throw in a handful of chilies.)

1433
01:07:46,572 --> 01:07:49,042
(Scoop it up, and it's ready.)

1434
01:07:49,842 --> 01:07:52,341
(A lot of meat)

1435
01:07:52,342 --> 01:07:54,681
(Radish and chilies)

1436
01:07:54,682 --> 01:07:57,212
(Repeat so it has a lot of everything.)

1437
01:07:57,882 --> 01:08:00,682
(While braised beef ribs is being prepared in the kitchen,)

1438
01:08:01,552 --> 01:08:04,352
(the floor starts its routine.)

1439
01:08:04,622 --> 01:08:07,692
(Routine 1: Prepare pickled vegetables as a side dish.)

1440
01:08:08,222 --> 01:08:11,632
(Plate an even amount of tomatoes and cucumbers.)

1441
01:08:11,862 --> 01:08:14,432
(He prepares as many as needed.)

1442
01:08:14,962 --> 01:08:17,832
(Routine 2: Prepare the rice so they're ready to be served.)

1443
01:08:18,502 --> 01:08:23,372
(Routine 3: Set up a portable stove.)

1444
01:08:25,012 --> 01:08:27,742
(What is this for?)

1445
01:08:28,342 --> 01:08:30,382
This is from Korea.

1446
01:08:30,552 --> 01:08:33,622
(Speaking clearly in Korean)

1447
01:08:34,322 --> 01:08:37,122
We can't get this here.

1448
01:08:37,852 --> 01:08:41,162
(Fiddling with the new technology)

1449
01:08:41,822 --> 01:08:43,492
What's in here?

1450
01:08:43,832 --> 01:08:46,802
I think the gel is the fuel.

1451
01:08:46,932 --> 01:08:48,972
(He can't take his eyes off of it.)

1452
01:08:49,832 --> 01:08:52,172
(He even tries to disassemble it.)

1453
01:08:53,302 --> 01:08:54,542
Don't break it.

1454
01:08:55,972 --> 01:08:58,582
(The playful dad wants to do it more because he's told not to.)

1455
01:08:58,842 --> 01:09:01,242
I could fit this in a bag.

1456
01:09:01,882 --> 01:09:03,782
If it fits in a bag, let's take it home.

1457
01:09:03,882 --> 01:09:06,552
(Dad, what are you doing?)

1458
01:09:06,822 --> 01:09:08,051
(Laughing)

1459
01:09:08,052 --> 01:09:09,152
Don't fool around.

1460
01:09:10,522 --> 01:09:13,361
(Since I can't have the stove, let me tap it at least.)

1461
01:09:13,362 --> 01:09:16,332
(While Si Jin's dad has his eyes on the stove...)

1462
01:09:16,892 --> 01:09:19,002
- Carefully.
- Carefully.

1463
01:09:20,732 --> 01:09:22,732
Here's your braised beef ribs.

1464
01:09:24,202 --> 01:09:25,232
Okay.

1465
01:09:25,302 --> 01:09:27,771
(At that time, Dad asks something.)

1466
01:09:27,772 --> 01:09:29,072
Will rice be served?

1467
01:09:29,572 --> 01:09:31,272
Yes, it will. Don't worry, Dad.

1468
01:09:34,642 --> 01:09:37,712
(Here's your awaited rice!)

1469
01:09:39,222 --> 01:09:41,751
Let us know if you need more rice.

1470
01:09:41,752 --> 01:09:43,651
It's bottomless.

1471
01:09:43,652 --> 01:09:44,822
- Okay.
- Okay.

1472
01:09:45,862 --> 01:09:47,261
Bon appetit.

1473
01:09:47,262 --> 01:09:50,332
(Enjoy your food.)

1474
01:09:51,132 --> 01:09:53,802
(Mom immediately takes a piece of radish!)

1475
01:09:54,532 --> 01:09:57,001
(Blowing it)

1476
01:09:57,002 --> 01:09:59,902
(A bite of radish)

1477
01:10:00,342 --> 01:10:03,211
(But Dad rummages through food instead of eating it.)

1478
01:10:03,212 --> 01:10:06,311
(Flipping the meat)

1479
01:10:06,312 --> 01:10:09,182
(He flips the meat one by one?)

1480
01:10:09,852 --> 01:10:12,021
(Gulping)

1481
01:10:12,022 --> 01:10:14,552
(He holds himself from eating it and looks quite serious.)

1482
01:10:15,052 --> 01:10:16,622
It isn't pork belly, honey.

1483
01:10:16,722 --> 01:10:19,562
(Go ahead and eat it.)

1484
01:10:19,992 --> 01:10:23,392
I'm trying to prevent the meat from becoming dry.

1485
01:10:23,692 --> 01:10:25,031
(His firm belief in food)

1486
01:10:25,032 --> 01:10:27,062
(The meat in braised beef ribs must not get dry.)

1487
01:10:27,402 --> 01:10:30,432
(He chooses a piece of moist meat soaked in the sauce.)

1488
01:10:31,072 --> 01:10:33,872
(He puts some rice onto the plate.)

1489
01:10:35,072 --> 01:10:37,112
(Adding some sauce)

1490
01:10:37,512 --> 01:10:39,682
(Adding more sauce)

1491
01:10:40,082 --> 01:10:44,652
(His firm belief in food part 2: The rice must not get dry either.)

1492
01:10:45,622 --> 01:10:47,682
(He eats a piece of moist meat.)

1493
01:10:49,092 --> 01:10:51,322
(Next, he eats a spoonful of moist rice.)

1494
01:10:53,162 --> 01:10:55,592
(Another spoonful)

1495
01:10:55,962 --> 01:10:57,031
It's delicious.

1496
01:10:57,032 --> 01:10:58,932
(He speaks important words in Korean.)

1497
01:11:00,102 --> 01:11:02,502
(Mom takes a bite of the meat too.)

1498
01:11:03,632 --> 01:11:06,602
(Following her husband, she takes some sauce to keep it moist.)

1499
01:11:07,042 --> 01:11:09,542
(Satisfied)

1500
01:11:10,212 --> 01:11:12,012
It tastes better with the sauce.

1501
01:11:12,512 --> 01:11:13,842
That's why you must flip these.

1502
01:11:14,242 --> 01:11:16,882
(She acknowledges it.)

1503
01:11:17,512 --> 01:11:20,622
(Now that his belief's acknowledged, he flips the meat excitedly.)

1504
01:11:21,652 --> 01:11:24,092
(After flipping them vigorously, he eats another piece of meat.)

1505
01:11:24,352 --> 01:11:26,762
(Yes, this is it!)

1506
01:11:29,432 --> 01:11:33,831
(This time, he adds the sauce a lot more boldly.)

1507
01:11:33,832 --> 01:11:36,502
(The rice becomes more moist.)

1508
01:11:37,532 --> 01:11:40,702
(He adds a lot of sauce,)

1509
01:11:41,042 --> 01:11:43,512
(so it becomes a lot tastier!)

1510
01:11:43,842 --> 01:11:46,042
(Scraping)

1511
01:11:47,482 --> 01:11:50,912
(He clears the whole bowl of rice.)

1512
01:11:51,752 --> 01:11:55,692
(While they enjoy braised beef ribs)

1513
01:11:55,922 --> 01:11:57,021
Have your parents...

1514
01:11:57,022 --> 01:11:58,122
- ordered drinks yet?
- No.

1515
01:11:58,552 --> 01:12:00,292
Then I should give them the drinks for free.

1516
01:12:01,762 --> 01:12:02,861
(It's Yu Ri's treat!)

1517
01:12:02,862 --> 01:12:05,392
Coke Zero and soda. They don't drink alcohol,

1518
01:12:05,632 --> 01:12:07,001
do they? No, right?

1519
01:12:07,002 --> 01:12:08,461
Dad is banned from drinking.

1520
01:12:08,462 --> 01:12:10,102
(Stern daughter)

1521
01:12:10,532 --> 01:12:11,931
Thank you.

1522
01:12:11,932 --> 01:12:13,742
(She prepares non-alcoholic drinks.)

1523
01:12:15,072 --> 01:12:17,311
Mother, Father, thank you.

1524
01:12:17,312 --> 01:12:19,141
Thank you so much.

1525
01:12:19,142 --> 01:12:20,242
It's nothing.

1526
01:12:20,412 --> 01:12:21,941
She works so hard.

1527
01:12:21,942 --> 01:12:23,482
- Thanks to her...
- Is she doing well?

1528
01:12:23,582 --> 01:12:27,282
Yes. Thanks to her, our work is so much easier.

1529
01:12:27,822 --> 01:12:29,421
- Thank you.
- No worries.

1530
01:12:29,422 --> 01:12:30,852
(Witty Yu Ri gives them free drinks and compliments Si Jin too.)

1531
01:12:31,592 --> 01:12:34,022
(Thanks to her, Mom smiles brightly.)

1532
01:12:34,722 --> 01:12:35,992
Dad, do you need more rice?

1533
01:12:36,762 --> 01:12:39,201
(Si Jin comes and checks for a rice refill.)

1534
01:12:39,202 --> 01:12:41,701
- Mine's left. He can have this.
- It's fine.

1535
01:12:41,702 --> 01:12:43,102
- He can have mine.
- Give me more rice.

1536
01:12:43,832 --> 01:12:44,871
I'll bring one.

1537
01:12:44,872 --> 01:12:46,102
(Speaking clearly in case she doesn't give him rice)

1538
01:12:46,802 --> 01:12:50,042
(Si Jin quickly scoops up a bowl of rice.)

1539
01:12:50,642 --> 01:12:52,511
This is a refill.

1540
01:12:52,512 --> 01:12:54,111
(Serving it to Dad without looking at him)

1541
01:12:54,112 --> 01:12:56,712
(Very cool)

1542
01:12:57,952 --> 01:12:59,182
That's too much rice.

1543
01:13:00,622 --> 01:13:03,992
I think Si Jin brought a lot for you.

1544
01:13:04,622 --> 01:13:05,961
(The rice full of Si Jin's love)

1545
01:13:05,962 --> 01:13:07,992
- It's not salty.
- You'll finish it all?

1546
01:13:08,362 --> 01:13:10,791
(Not much braised beef ribs sauce is left.)

1547
01:13:10,792 --> 01:13:14,731
(He tilts the pan and scrapes up the sauce.)

1548
01:13:14,732 --> 01:13:16,131
(Using the Korean skill,)

1549
01:13:16,132 --> 01:13:17,572
(he collects the sauce and pours it onto the rice.)

1550
01:13:18,202 --> 01:13:20,202
- It's so delicious.
- Is it?

1551
01:13:23,442 --> 01:13:27,542
(Rice with braised beef ribs is impossible to taste bad.)

1552
01:13:28,382 --> 01:13:31,581
(Scraping)

1553
01:13:31,582 --> 01:13:34,752
(He's already done with the refilled rice.)

1554
01:13:36,452 --> 01:13:39,161
(He now takes his wife's leftover rice...)

1555
01:13:39,162 --> 01:13:42,692
(and pours it onto the pan!)

1556
01:13:43,462 --> 01:13:47,202
(He mixes and mixes the rice.)

1557
01:13:47,762 --> 01:13:51,472
(He eats nonstop.)

1558
01:13:51,902 --> 01:13:53,801
(A cleared pan...)

1559
01:13:53,802 --> 01:13:56,912
(and three empty bowls of rice)

1560
01:13:57,642 --> 01:13:59,882
(Satisfied)

1561
01:14:00,312 --> 01:14:02,752
(Meanwhile, the kitchen has some breathing room.)

1562
01:14:03,252 --> 01:14:05,921
(The floor takes a breather too.)

1563
01:14:05,922 --> 01:14:08,322
(Something catches Yu Ri's eyes.)

1564
01:14:08,922 --> 01:14:11,792
(The customers are eating just the basic side dishes.)

1565
01:14:13,222 --> 01:14:15,662
When will the food for Table One be ready? Are you making it now?

1566
01:14:16,292 --> 01:14:18,232
- When will Table One be ready?
- They're already served.

1567
01:14:18,692 --> 01:14:19,932
- Wait, what?
- Table One?

1568
01:14:22,102 --> 01:14:24,932
(A pan is being boiled on its own by the window.)

1569
01:14:25,002 --> 01:14:26,801
The food for Table One is served. It didn't?

1570
01:14:26,802 --> 01:14:28,302
- It did.
- It didn't.

1571
01:14:29,212 --> 01:14:31,171
- Table One didn't get the food.
- It didn't.

1572
01:14:31,172 --> 01:14:32,912
(Table 1 doesn't have a pan!)

1573
01:14:33,412 --> 01:14:35,282
Didn't Si Jin take it just now?

1574
01:14:35,542 --> 01:14:40,022
(The whole order disappeared?)

1575
01:14:40,292 --> 01:14:42,321
The food for Table One is served. It didn't?

1576
01:14:42,322 --> 01:14:43,562
- It did.
- It didn't.

1577
01:14:44,522 --> 01:14:46,361
- Table One didn't get the food.
- It didn't.

1578
01:14:46,362 --> 01:14:48,192
(Table 1 doesn't have a pan!)

1579
01:14:48,732 --> 01:14:50,502
Didn't Si Jin take it just now?

1580
01:14:50,862 --> 01:14:54,132
(Something went wrong.)

1581
01:14:54,572 --> 01:14:56,842
(Reconstructing the event)

1582
01:14:57,202 --> 01:14:58,271
(Exposition)

1583
01:14:58,272 --> 01:15:00,812
(Jang Woo saw the pan for Table 1 placed next to the window.)

1584
01:15:01,072 --> 01:15:03,242
- The pan for Table 1 will be ready.
- Table 1, okay.

1585
01:15:03,612 --> 01:15:04,612
(Rising action)

1586
01:15:04,613 --> 01:15:06,752
(He said the food for Table 1 would be ready.)

1587
01:15:07,212 --> 01:15:09,951
(Jang Woo said so, but he didn't actually serve the pan.)

1588
01:15:09,952 --> 01:15:12,791
(Si Jin left the spot suddenly.)

1589
01:15:12,792 --> 01:15:15,622
(Climax)

1590
01:15:15,822 --> 01:15:17,591
(The order sheet for Table One)

1591
01:15:17,592 --> 01:15:19,132
Table One is served.

1592
01:15:20,262 --> 01:15:21,331
(Falling action)

1593
01:15:21,332 --> 01:15:23,702
(He removed the order sheet for Table 1, which wasn't served.)

1594
01:15:23,932 --> 01:15:26,631
(Just like that, the pan was left unattended.)

1595
01:15:26,632 --> 01:15:27,871
- Get a grip.
- Table One...

1596
01:15:27,872 --> 01:15:28,931
(He's scolded.)

1597
01:15:28,932 --> 01:15:30,172
The food wasn't served.

1598
01:15:30,502 --> 01:15:32,101
Triple scoldings.

1599
01:15:32,102 --> 01:15:33,872
(He achieves triple scoldings.)

1600
01:15:34,742 --> 01:15:36,081
(He gets himself together and quickly makes a pan.)

1601
01:15:36,082 --> 01:15:37,412
It's pretty. Table One.

1602
01:15:38,142 --> 01:15:41,252
(Yu Ri quickly serves it.)

1603
01:15:41,852 --> 01:15:44,222
It looks good.

1604
01:15:44,852 --> 01:15:48,152
(Yu Ri checks on them until the very end.)

1605
01:15:49,762 --> 01:15:50,762
(Glancing)

1606
01:15:53,032 --> 01:15:55,592
They're mixing rice with the sauce. They're enjoying it.

1607
01:15:56,762 --> 01:15:58,062
They're scraping their plates.

1608
01:16:02,842 --> 01:16:06,912
(They scrape down to the final grain of rice.)

1609
01:16:09,182 --> 01:16:13,712
(Perfect)

1610
01:16:14,082 --> 01:16:15,512
- I should cook more rice.
- Yes.

1611
01:16:16,582 --> 01:16:18,222
- Ten more minutes should do.
- Sorry?

1612
01:16:18,382 --> 01:16:20,092
Ten more minutes should do.

1613
01:16:21,122 --> 01:16:22,761
(Current time: 1:30pm)

1614
01:16:22,762 --> 01:16:25,721
(It's been 1 hour and 30 minutes since opening.)

1615
01:16:25,722 --> 01:16:27,891
- Thank you.
- Thank you. Bye.

1616
01:16:27,892 --> 01:16:29,201
(Customers start to leave one after another.)

1617
01:16:29,202 --> 01:16:30,362
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1618
01:16:31,502 --> 01:16:32,602
Thank you.

1619
01:16:33,372 --> 01:16:36,141
(Si Jin's parents have finished their meal.)

1620
01:16:36,142 --> 01:16:37,442
Did you enjoy the food?

1621
01:16:38,042 --> 01:16:39,272
Thank you.

1622
01:16:40,142 --> 01:16:42,882
Si Jin is so pretty and kind.

1623
01:16:43,042 --> 01:16:44,982
She was of great help.

1624
01:16:45,912 --> 01:16:47,012
I paid for you.

1625
01:16:49,052 --> 01:16:50,621
- Bye, Mom. See you later.
- Bye.

1626
01:16:50,622 --> 01:16:52,082
Thank you. Goodbye.

1627
01:16:54,292 --> 01:16:55,392
Thank you.

1628
01:16:57,262 --> 01:17:00,862
(Si Jin's parents leave too.)

1629
01:17:01,892 --> 01:17:06,432
(The once full-house outdoor seats now have some empty seats.)

1630
01:17:07,472 --> 01:17:10,172
(A restaurant having empty seats means...)

1631
01:17:10,742 --> 01:17:13,572
(it is ready to accept new customers.)

1632
01:17:14,272 --> 01:17:16,241
(2 new customers)

1633
01:17:16,242 --> 01:17:18,341
(4 new customers)

1634
01:17:18,342 --> 01:17:20,651
(6 new customers)

1635
01:17:20,652 --> 01:17:23,121
(7 new customers)

1636
01:17:23,122 --> 01:17:25,422
(9 new customers)

1637
01:17:29,122 --> 01:17:31,462
It's just one person. If it's okay, I'll eat outside.

1638
01:17:33,032 --> 01:17:35,462
(A total of 10 people have entered, including the one eating alone.)

1639
01:17:35,902 --> 01:17:37,562
We're having the biggest lunch crowd.

1640
01:17:37,632 --> 01:17:40,331
Yes. Of the lunches we've had, we're busiest...

1641
01:17:40,332 --> 01:17:42,432
- It's the most crowded.
- today, right?

1642
01:17:43,472 --> 01:17:45,442
- Yu Ri, this is for Table 11.
- Okay.

1643
01:17:47,442 --> 01:17:49,412
- Hello.
- Hi.

1644
01:17:49,812 --> 01:17:51,382
This is tteokbokki.

1645
01:17:52,342 --> 01:17:53,812
Please enjoy.

1646
01:17:54,682 --> 01:17:56,982
(Glancing)

1647
01:17:57,852 --> 01:18:01,052
(She ties her hair as it's a hot day.)

1648
01:18:02,122 --> 01:18:06,292
(And the other guest cools himself down with a beer.)

1649
01:18:08,032 --> 01:18:10,862
Goodness. It's really hot outside.

1650
01:18:12,002 --> 01:18:15,102
(It's so hot that even the locals who love the sun are struggling.)

1651
01:18:23,082 --> 01:18:29,352
(Yu Ri grabs something from the fridge.)

1652
01:18:31,022 --> 01:18:32,122
Are you hot?

1653
01:18:32,422 --> 01:18:33,522
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1654
01:18:34,252 --> 01:18:37,762
(What are these?)

1655
01:18:39,832 --> 01:18:41,461
(They're neck coolers for the customers who find it hot.)

1656
01:18:41,462 --> 01:18:43,401
Gosh. This is a great idea.

1657
01:18:43,402 --> 01:18:44,562
I love it.

1658
01:18:45,662 --> 01:18:48,231
(They put it around their necks right away.)

1659
01:18:48,232 --> 01:18:49,672
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1660
01:18:50,802 --> 01:18:53,442
It's a great way to beat the heat.

1661
01:18:54,142 --> 01:18:55,341
My goodness.

1662
01:18:55,342 --> 01:18:58,182
Why do we not have things like this?

1663
01:18:59,582 --> 01:19:01,152
Look what we've got.

1664
01:19:02,922 --> 01:19:04,752
That's very Asian.

1665
01:19:05,552 --> 01:19:07,821
My girlfriend told me...

1666
01:19:07,822 --> 01:19:11,222
there's even a thing where the air blows from the back.

1667
01:19:11,862 --> 01:19:14,492
(He's probably talking about this.)

1668
01:19:14,832 --> 01:19:18,662
Koreans are living in the future.

1669
01:19:19,732 --> 01:19:21,501
- What? It's cold.
- Don't you want one?

1670
01:19:21,502 --> 01:19:23,972
(The future hates it.)

1671
01:19:25,702 --> 01:19:27,512
Do you like tteokbokki?

1672
01:19:30,042 --> 01:19:31,312
We love it.

1673
01:19:32,712 --> 01:19:36,552
(Adding lots of love into tteokbokki)

1674
01:19:37,652 --> 01:19:40,092
(Approaching quietly)

1675
01:19:43,022 --> 01:19:46,292
(Tteokbokki)

1676
01:19:48,232 --> 01:19:50,602
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1677
01:19:58,272 --> 01:20:00,042
(Eating)

1678
01:20:02,042 --> 01:20:03,311
(Eating)

1679
01:20:03,312 --> 01:20:07,082
(Savoring it with her eyes closed)

1680
01:20:08,012 --> 01:20:09,012
It's good.

1681
01:20:14,022 --> 01:20:17,262
(While they enjoy a bit of relaxation,)

1682
01:20:18,292 --> 01:20:22,192
(the customers start to leave one by one.)

1683
01:20:23,402 --> 01:20:25,501
- Do you like it?
- Thank you. Yes.

1684
01:20:25,502 --> 01:20:28,832
I'll put it in my freezer and use it forever.

1685
01:20:29,802 --> 01:20:32,272
Thank you very much.

1686
01:20:32,742 --> 01:20:34,541
- Bye.
- Thank you.

1687
01:20:34,542 --> 01:20:36,141
- Bye.
- Bye.

1688
01:20:36,142 --> 01:20:38,512
(The customers with the souvenirs have also left.)

1689
01:20:39,352 --> 01:20:42,152
(Single Pan House is quiet after the customers left.)

1690
01:20:42,512 --> 01:20:44,522
(Is Chef Paik putting on the gloves again?)

1691
01:20:44,952 --> 01:20:47,022
How many do I have to prepare? How many restaurants are there?

1692
01:20:47,422 --> 01:20:49,291
I'll pack some braised beef ribs.

1693
01:20:49,292 --> 01:20:51,991
Visit the restaurants together,

1694
01:20:51,992 --> 01:20:53,832
- Okay.
- and give them the gifts.

1695
01:20:54,132 --> 01:20:55,862
- Tell them thank you.
- Yes.

1696
01:20:56,202 --> 01:20:58,701
Do we pack it in the transparent containers?

1697
01:20:58,702 --> 01:21:00,132
It doesn't matter. Give one to me.

1698
01:21:00,702 --> 01:21:05,142
(Chef Paik prepares the thank-you gifts.)

1699
01:21:05,572 --> 01:21:08,712
(Adding a generous amount to each to-go container)

1700
01:21:08,872 --> 01:21:11,782
(After adding a big portion of the braised beef ribs,)

1701
01:21:12,242 --> 01:21:14,652
(Jang Woo, the sous chef,)

1702
01:21:15,052 --> 01:21:18,682
(prepares jeon that will go with the beef ribs.)

1703
01:21:20,722 --> 01:21:25,162
(After cooking the whole grill of the jeon into golden brown,)

1704
01:21:25,692 --> 01:21:28,692
(he puts them in the container carefully.)

1705
01:21:29,092 --> 01:21:31,031
(With the braised beef ribs, today's main dish,)

1706
01:21:31,032 --> 01:21:33,502
(and assorted jeon,)

1707
01:21:34,002 --> 01:21:36,802
(Chef Paik's gift is ready!)

1708
01:21:37,272 --> 01:21:40,012
(They take the containers packed with love.)

1709
01:21:40,242 --> 01:21:41,342
Let's go.

1710
01:21:41,412 --> 01:21:42,712
Do we leave now?

1711
01:21:42,842 --> 01:21:44,042
Yes. Right now.

1712
01:21:44,442 --> 01:21:46,812
(The first restaurant to hand the gift is...)

1713
01:21:47,482 --> 01:21:49,982
- The burger place!
- Right. The burger place.

1714
01:21:50,782 --> 01:21:52,791
- Excuse me.
- Hello.

1715
01:21:52,792 --> 01:21:53,852
(Burger Place P was always number 1 in sales.)

1716
01:21:55,692 --> 01:21:58,122
This is our menu today.

1717
01:21:58,292 --> 01:22:00,931
- Thank you so much.
- Bye.

1718
01:22:00,932 --> 01:22:02,392
(They expressed their gratitude with the gift.)

1719
01:22:03,502 --> 01:22:06,031
This is our little gift.

1720
01:22:06,032 --> 01:22:07,232
Thank you.

1721
01:22:07,272 --> 01:22:09,902
(The restaurants on Rue Merciere gladly joined...)

1722
01:22:10,872 --> 01:22:13,811
(in the friendly sales competition with the Single Pan House.)

1723
01:22:13,812 --> 01:22:16,681
- Thank you very much, friends!
- Thank you very much.

1724
01:22:16,682 --> 01:22:17,712
Bye.

1725
01:22:18,442 --> 01:22:20,712
- To the last place. Let's go.
- Let's go.

1726
01:22:21,082 --> 01:22:23,622
(The last place they visit is...)

1727
01:22:24,022 --> 01:22:25,881
- Hello.
- Hi.

1728
01:22:25,882 --> 01:22:28,552
- Samuel, I was looking for you.
- It's him.

1729
01:22:30,662 --> 01:22:32,892
(the Italian Restaurant M.)

1730
01:22:33,632 --> 01:22:34,661
(The owner happens to be sitting outside.)

1731
01:22:34,662 --> 01:22:36,131
Sorry to bother you when you're eating.

1732
01:22:36,132 --> 01:22:37,931
It's our little presents.

1733
01:22:37,932 --> 01:22:39,601
- Gosh.
- It's our menu today.

1734
01:22:39,602 --> 01:22:40,871
- Okay.
- Yes.

1735
01:22:40,872 --> 01:22:43,041
Thank you so much.

1736
01:22:43,042 --> 01:22:44,702
(Touched)

1737
01:22:44,902 --> 01:22:46,712
Today was our last day.

1738
01:22:47,072 --> 01:22:49,011
Thank you for everything.

1739
01:22:49,012 --> 01:22:51,082
John, do you want to come to my place to work?

1740
01:22:52,442 --> 01:22:53,851
You can come if you want. It's okay.

1741
01:22:53,852 --> 01:22:55,112
- I saw you working.
- Yes.

1742
01:22:55,212 --> 01:22:56,481
- You can come.
- Am I okay?

1743
01:22:56,482 --> 01:22:58,122
You're okay. You're more than "okay."

1744
01:22:58,352 --> 01:22:59,591
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

1745
01:22:59,592 --> 01:23:01,622
- Thank you so much, guys.
- Thank you.

1746
01:23:01,822 --> 01:23:03,421
- Gosh.
- We're back.

1747
01:23:03,422 --> 01:23:04,522
Good job.

1748
01:23:04,892 --> 01:23:06,192
Great job today.

1749
01:23:07,292 --> 01:23:09,732
(At that moment,)

1750
01:23:10,232 --> 01:23:12,872
(the owner of Restaurant M comes into the Single Pan House.)

1751
01:23:13,272 --> 01:23:14,672
(Surprised)

1752
01:23:15,402 --> 01:23:16,742
A present for you.

1753
01:23:18,842 --> 01:23:20,111
(He has brought a bottle of wine as a gift.)

1754
01:23:20,112 --> 01:23:22,111
- I hope you enjoy wine.
- Hold on.

1755
01:23:22,112 --> 01:23:24,042
- I hope it's okay for you.
- Thank you.

1756
01:23:25,882 --> 01:23:27,452
Thank you.

1757
01:23:27,912 --> 01:23:30,552
Gosh. Big chef. Please.

1758
01:23:31,622 --> 01:23:34,551
- Thank you for everything, Chef.
- Goodness.

1759
01:23:34,552 --> 01:23:35,921
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1760
01:23:35,922 --> 01:23:37,322
(The two owners thank each other as they didn't get to before.)

1761
01:23:37,522 --> 01:23:39,561
(Grabbing)

1762
01:23:39,562 --> 01:23:42,061
- Samuel, take this. It's makgeolli.
- No, it's okay.

1763
01:23:42,062 --> 01:23:43,231
- No.
- Please.

1764
01:23:43,232 --> 01:23:45,202
We have so many here.

1765
01:23:45,532 --> 01:23:47,972
- Thank you.
- It's just a souvenir.

1766
01:23:49,102 --> 01:23:51,201
- Thank you for everything.
- Thank you.

1767
01:23:51,202 --> 01:23:53,011
- We appreciate it, Samuel.
- Bye.

1768
01:23:53,012 --> 01:23:55,042
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

1769
01:23:55,342 --> 01:23:57,582
(The feeling of warmth was only for a moment.)

1770
01:23:57,742 --> 01:24:00,552
(What is important is the final sales figure!)

1771
01:24:00,782 --> 01:24:02,212
How much did we sell today?

1772
01:24:03,722 --> 01:24:07,092
(With only 100 euros left to make, they opened for the last day.)

1773
01:24:07,992 --> 01:24:12,022
(With the constant rush of customers since the opening...)

1774
01:24:12,262 --> 01:24:14,992
(I think we've reached our goal already.)

1775
01:24:15,532 --> 01:24:17,062
- Chef Paik.
- Yes?

1776
01:24:18,132 --> 01:24:19,201
(They've reached the sales target!)

1777
01:24:19,202 --> 01:24:20,872
(Bowing)

1778
01:24:22,332 --> 01:24:23,601
(What is the result...)

1779
01:24:23,602 --> 01:24:26,272
(when they kept going after passing the goal?)

1780
01:24:26,412 --> 01:24:29,272
How much do you expect the sales to be?

1781
01:24:29,642 --> 01:24:31,012
I'd say 1,150 euros.

1782
01:24:33,052 --> 01:24:34,452
Then, I'll go with 1,200 euros.

1783
01:24:35,482 --> 01:24:36,722
I'd say 1,050 euros.

1784
01:24:37,552 --> 01:24:39,482
(The numbers are very specific.)

1785
01:24:39,522 --> 01:24:41,922
What if I was right, surprising everyone?

1786
01:24:43,792 --> 01:24:44,822
You'll see.

1787
01:24:45,292 --> 01:24:46,862
The sales for the lunch were...

1788
01:24:47,232 --> 01:24:49,632
(What is the figure for the day 8 sales?)

1789
01:24:50,602 --> 01:24:52,161
It's 1,055 euros.

1790
01:24:52,162 --> 01:24:55,632
Gosh. You got it right, Si Yoon.

1791
01:24:55,932 --> 01:24:58,002
- You got it right.
- I told you.

1792
01:24:58,272 --> 01:25:01,072
I can tell by doing the dishes.

1793
01:25:01,312 --> 01:25:02,372
Seriously.

1794
01:25:06,612 --> 01:25:08,151
- Gosh. It goes over the letters.
- Gosh.

1795
01:25:08,152 --> 01:25:10,481
(Total in sales)

1796
01:25:10,482 --> 01:25:11,552
Good job.

1797
01:25:12,482 --> 01:25:15,391
This is truly amazing. It's...

1798
01:25:15,392 --> 01:25:19,361
Usually... I know it because I do business. It's crazy.

1799
01:25:19,362 --> 01:25:20,862
(We finally did it.)

1800
01:25:22,392 --> 01:25:26,302
(Chef Paik completed the mission for the first time.)

1801
01:25:26,472 --> 01:25:28,972
(In fact, Chef Paik...)

1802
01:25:32,202 --> 01:25:34,872
(went to unfamiliar countries out of the blue...)

1803
01:25:35,412 --> 01:25:40,212
(and tried three times in Morocco, Italy, and Spain.)

1804
01:25:40,982 --> 01:25:45,552
(And he failed three times.)

1805
01:25:46,522 --> 01:25:48,822
(It's a shame. We needed just a little more.)

1806
01:25:48,992 --> 01:25:51,622
(And...)

1807
01:25:52,092 --> 01:25:54,832
(he made his fourth attempt in France, the culinary powerhouse.)

1808
01:25:55,062 --> 01:25:57,731
(He aimed for the annual sales of 1 million dollars.)

1809
01:25:57,732 --> 01:25:59,132
(Single Pan House)

1810
01:25:59,562 --> 01:26:02,572
(He sharpened his knives and prepared...)

1811
01:26:05,142 --> 01:26:07,112
(meat.)

1812
01:26:07,272 --> 01:26:09,071
(He put all kinds of meat on a single pan!)

1813
01:26:09,072 --> 01:26:10,342
